Package io.honeycomb.libhoney

Class LibHoney

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.honeycomb.libhoney.LibHoney

  • public final class LibHoney
extends Object

    The entry point to the honeycomb client library, used to create a HoneyClient.

    Use options() to set configuration options, and pass them to create(Options) to create a HoneyClient instance. The configuration options are documented on Options.Builder's setters. All configuration options are optional, and Options holds the default values for any that do not get explicitly set.
    Usage and other details are documented on HoneyClient.

    Default client

    You can use setDefault(HoneyClient) (or call HoneyClient.setAsDefault() directly on an instance) to set a globally accesible client instance, then retrievable via getDefault().

      • closeOnShutdown

        public static void closeOnShutdown​(HoneyClient client)
        Utility to add a JVM shutdown hook that invokes HoneyClient.close() on the provided client instance. Note that this will keep a strong reference to the instance, so should only be used if it is expected to live for the lifetime of the application.
        Parameters:
        client - to close when the JVM shuts down.
